  "text": "Physiological changes during pregnancy are significant and their knowledge is essential to optimize outcomes. Volemia augmentation in pregnancy averages 40-45% above the nonpregnant blood volume after 32-34 weeks. Cardiac output is increased as early as the 5th week and reflects a reduced systemic vascular resistance and an increased heart rate [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
